obo:GO_0003674  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_72  a       owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Using STORM super resolution microscopy and well-validated antibodies, it is demonstrated that RIM1/2 is localized at the active zone, directly opposed to PSD95. RIM1/2 localization is very similar to other well-validated active zone components, including Munc13 and Bassoon (Figure 1). RIM1/2 localization is also shown to correlate with the location of vesicle fusion (Figure 2).\n\n23/01/2017 Pim\n- The RIM antibody (anti-RIM1/2 (1:500; Synaptic Systems No. 140203) used in Fig. 1 has a non-selective RIM1/RIM2 specificity.\n- The authors mention identical results with a RIM1 specific antibody (\"Similar distribution and nanocluster properties were found using a different antibody targeted towards a separate epitope in RIM1 (Extended Data Fig. 2d)\").\n- presynaptic localization of overexpressed RIM1 is shown in Fig.2 (\"To assess these predictions, we mapped vesicle fusion sites relative to Eos3-tagged RIM1 using sequential PALM-pHuse imaging on the same live boutons (Fig. 2h, Extended Data Fig. 6d, e)\")\n- Overall these data justify annotation against RIM1.. Experimental description: Dissociated hippocampal neurons from E18 SD rats of both sexes were prepared as described previously31." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-03-21" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_72" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

